@ezyang the rationale for `return {x, y}` is in e.g.
```
VeryLongToTypeAnnoyingName foo(...) {
  return VeryLongToTypeAnnoyingName(x, y);
}
```

The type is already clear from the return value, so it's more neat to write

```
VeryLongToTypeAnnoyingName foo(...) {
  return {x, y};
}
```
